1a:["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","code",null,{"children":"KredioAccountRegistry"}]," binds an EVM address to a Substrate (SR25519) public key. The user provides a valid SR25519 signature over a structured payload containing their EVM address and a nonce. The registry verifies it on-chain using the Asset Hub System precompile's ",["$","code",null,{"children":"sr25519Verify"}]," function and creates a bidirectional, nonce-protected mapping. Replay attacks are blocked by nonce increment on both link and unlink."]}]
1b:["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","code",null,{"children":"GovernanceCache"}]," stores each user's OpenGov vote count and conviction level on-chain. In Phase 4 this data feeds directly into the ",["$","code",null,{"children":"KreditAgent"}]," scoring model - active governance participants earn a persistent credit bonus. The Polkadot ConvictionVoting precompile makes this natively queryable from Asset Hub contracts without any off-chain indexer."]}]
